						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Estlib wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">there does exist a standing sprite of the &quot;NES Vectorman&quot; but its way too big for anything else to exist on the screen (see attachment).</div><br /><br />Actually, it looks like you could get away with using several sprites instead of him being a 'solid' block of a character.  For example, his feet can be drawn with 4 titles total, and his legs could be overlayed sprites.  The graphics would need to be drawn and arranged in a very specific manner to use up as little sprites per scanline as possible.  You could get him to be 4 tiles wide if you're lucky, which would be enough for another enemy.  Alternatively, the enemies could be background based, since the entire stage is black and could easily hide the fact that they are backgrounds.</div>

